  <h1>Gem</h1>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki. <br></br>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/119280/">Oganesson897</style>, <br></br> <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/blackdragon2447">BlackDragon2447</style> <br></br></style>
  </text>
  <text>Gems are obtained either through <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/sifter" underlined="true">sifting</style> <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/purified_ore" underlined="true">purified gem ores</style>, being upgraded form <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/flawed_gem" underlined="true">Flawed Gem</style> or crafted form <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/flawless_gem" underlined="true">Flawless Gems</style>, normal gems have more uses, compared to the other qualities of gems. Normal Gems can be upgraded to <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/flawless_gem" underlined="true">Flawless Gems</style> in a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/laser_engraver" underlined="true">Laser Engraver</style>.</text>
  <recipe id="gtceu:sifter/sift_ruby_purified_ore_to_gems"></recipe>
  <recipe id="gtceu:laser_engraver/engrave_ruby_flawless_gem_to_gem"></recipe>
</page>
